<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--PrisonFight     08-28 0161</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Prison Fight,0166</SECOND>
<HEAD>Injures 32 Inmates</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MORAVIA, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A brawl in which inmates brandished barbells
injured 32 men at a medium-security prison, authorities said.
   About 200 inmates at the Cayuga Correctional Facility were in the
yard near some weight-lifting equipment when the fight broke out
Sunday night, said state corrections spokesman James Flateau.
   Guards broke up the fight and had the inmates back in their
dormitories within an hour, he said.
   ``The prison is secure,'' Flateau said early today.
   Six inmates were taken to a hospital Sunday night, and 26 were
treated at the prison infirmary, mostly for cuts and bruises,
Flateau said. No guards were hurt, he said.
   One of the six sent for outside treatment was seriously injured
and was being evaluated early today, said Art Perry, a Cortland
Memorial Hospital spokesman. The five other inmates were treated for
cuts and bruises.
   Officials at the central New York prison do not know what started
the fight.
