<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Belgium-AirShow     08-28 0140</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Belgium-Air Show,0141</SECOND>
<HEAD>First Show Since Ramstein for Italian Stunt Pilots</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Ramstein's Legacy</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHARLEROI, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Italian air force stunt team
involved in the air disaster a year ago today at Ramstein, West
Germany, made its first public performance since the accident that
killed 70 people.
   The Freece Tricolori's nine Aermachi jets on Sunday flew several
aerobatic stunts over an airport near this southern town, including
a modified version of the ``pierced heart'' routine in which three
planes crashed into each other last Aug. 28.
   ``We cannot forget what happened, but you have to overcome that
and try to do your job,'' said spokesman Lt. Col. Gianfranco da
Forno.
   The team performed more than 1,300 feet from the crowd of several
thousand people, almost twice the distance they used at Ramstein Air
Base a year ago.
</TEXT>
