<FIRST>r a PM-BRF--PartyShootings     08-28 0178</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Party Shootings,0183</SECOND>
<HEAD>Four Killed, Two Injured at Birthday Party</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An estranged husband showed up uninvited at a
birthday party and opened fire on guests, killing four and injuring
two.
   ``It was a family birthday party that turned into tragedy,''
sheriff's Deputy Dean Scoville said today.
   The alleged gunman, identified as Raymundo Navarro Jr., 26, fled
the scene, but surrendered to deputies early today. He was arrested
for investigation of murder, Scoville said.
   Three people died at the home in East Los Angeles following the
shooting late Sunday night. A fourth died early today at Santa Marta
Hospital and two other victims were taken to County-USC Medical
Center.
   The identities of the victims and the conditions of the survivors
were not immediately available. Authorities declined to say whether
Navarro's wife was among those shot.
   The two were planning to be divorced, according to Deputy Fidel
Gonzales. ``We believe that's where the motive lies,'' he said.
   The incident was part of weekend violence in Los Angeles that
took the lives of 16, police said.
</TEXT>
