<FIRST>r a PM-RussianRoulette     08-28 0167</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Russian Roulette,0171</SECOND>
<HEAD>New York Man Killed in 2nd Russian Roulette Death in 2 Days</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 24-year-old man killed himself this morning
while playing Russian roulette with a handgun, police said.
   The shooting of Brian Maher was the second death in two days
attributed to the deadly game.
   Maher and two friends went out drinking and then returned to his
apartment in Queens, where they played Russian roulette with a
.38-caliber revolver that had one bullet in the chamber, according
to a police spokeswoman, Officer Janice Swinney.
   Maher shot himself in the head at 7:20 a.m. and was pronounced
dead at the scene.
   Early Sunday, an off-duty New York City police officer, Joseph
Montalbano, 21, was allegedly shot to death by his girlfriend, Elisa
Beth Egger, 24, during a game of Russian roulette in his Holbrook,
N.Y., home.
   Ms. Egger told police she didn't realize the revolver was loaded,
Suffolk County police said. She was arrested on a charge of
second-degree manslaughter.
</TEXT>
