<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--ArrowDeath     08-28 0158</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Arrow Death,0161</SECOND>
<HEAD>Investigators Say Burglar Fell On Stolen Arrow</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SKIATOOK, Okla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A burglar died after he apparently
stumbled down a stairway and fell on a hunting arrow he was
carrying, investigators said today.
   Greg Moore, 25, of Tulsa, was found dead in his pickup truck
about three-fourths of a mile from a house in Skiatook that had been
ransacked early Sunday, according to Bill Williams, chief deputy at
the Osage County sheriff's office.
   Williams said a passing oil field worker found Moore slumped in
the pickup, with the lights on and horn blasting. Moore had a wound
in his lower chest that appeared to have severed a major artery,
Williams said.
   The deputy said cocaine, syringes and other drug paraphernalia,
along with goods stolen from the house, were found in the truck.
   Investigators found blood on the porch of the burglarized house
and a bloody hunting arrow and trails of blood inside, Williams said.
</TEXT>
