<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Japan-Storm     08-28 0104</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Japan-Storm,0106</SECOND>
<HEAD>Storm Leaves Three Dead, Three Missing as It Heads for Soviet Union</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A tropical storm that swept over Japan killed three
people, left three others missing, and flooded more than 1,000
houses, the National Police Agency reported Monday.
   The storm's heavy rain and 55 mph winds triggered flooding and
landslides, and injured 11 people, according to an agency official.
   The official said 1,071 houses were flooded, landslides were
reported at 85 places, and roads were destroyed at 120 sites in
western and northern Japan. The storm crossed from southwestern
Japan to the northernmost island of Hokkaido early Monday.
