<HEAD>$Adv10</HEAD>
<HEAD>AGENCIES AND RADIO OUT</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release Sunday, Sept. 10</HEAD>
<HEAD>From AP Newsfeatures</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of musicals and plays scheduled to
open on Broadway before Jan. 1. Dates and theaters are subject to
change.
   Musicals:
   ``Sweeney Todd,'' Sept. 14, Circle in the Square.
   ``Dangerous Games,'' Oct. 19, Nederlander Theater.
   ``Grand Hotel,'' Oct. 29, Martin Beck Theater.
   ``The Prince of Central Park,'' Oct. 30, Belasco Theater.
   ``Meet Me in St. Louis,'' Nov. 2, Gershwin Theater.
   ``3 Penny Opera,'' Nov. 5, Lunt-Fontanne Theater.
   ``Gypsy,'' Nov. 19, St. James Theater.
   ``City of Angels,'' Dec. 7, Virginia Theater.
   Plays:
   ``Orpheus Descending,'' Sept. 24, Neil Simon Theater.
   ``Mastergate,'' Oct. 12, Criterion Center.
   ``Tru,'' opening in October, date and theater not set.
   ``Secret Rapture,'' Nov. 6, Ethel Barrymore Theater.
   ``The Circle,'' Nov. 20, Ambassador Theater.
   ``A Few Good Men,'' opening in November at the Music Box Theater.
Date not set.
   ``Artist Descending a Staircase,'' Nov. 30, Helen Hayes Theater.
   ``The Merchant of Venice,'' Dec. 14, 46th Street Theater.
   ``The Tenth Man,'' opening in December at the Vivian Beaumont
Theater. Date not set.
