<FIRST>s a BC-APN--MuseumGivebacks-Quotes ADV10   08-28 0266</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-APN--Museum Givebacks-Quotes, ADV 10,0270</SECOND>
<HEAD>$Adv10</HEAD>
<HEAD>AGENCIES AND RADIO OUT</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release Sunday, Sept. 10</HEAD>
<HEAD>From AP Newsfeatures</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-APN--Museum Givebacks</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By HUGH A. MULLIGAN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Special Correspondent</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   A collection of quotes from collectors, curators and others
concerned about ethics in art collecting:
   ``Much blame attaches to those who destroyed so much in those
tombs, and it is the dealers and buyers who are the most to blame.''
_ Ian Graham, curator at Harvard's Peabody Museum, on the wholesale
looting of Guatemala's Rio Azul.
   ``Some of the most deplorable destruction of world art has
occurred with the full knowledge and complicity of the patrician
denizens of the museum and art world.'' _ Karl E. Meyer, author of
``The Plundered Past.''
   ``If you honor the claim of the Greek Orthodox Church,
potentially you denude our museums.'' _ Andre Emmerich, past
president of the Art Dealers Association of America, testifying at
the Indianapolis mosaics trial.
   ``Hell, yes, it was smuggled. I spent between $15 million and $16
million over the last two years on Asian art, and most of it was
smuggled.'' _California collector Norton Simon on his acquisition of
a bronze Hindu statue stolen from a village in Madras.
   ``Until excavation can be replaced by other exploratory
techniques, there is no escaping the fact that archaeology itself,
no matter how sophisticated the methodology, is a destructive
process.'' _ Ellen Herscher, member of the American Association of
Museums.
   ``If the loss of sites continues unchecked, archaeology in 2050
will be a dictionary word describing a defunct profession.'' _ Art
consultant Ruthann Knudson in Archaeology Magazine.
</TEXT>
