<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Matsushita     08-28 0211</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Matsushita,0218</SECOND>
<HEAD>Matsushita Reports Higher Earnings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Matsushita Electric Industrial Co. Ltd. said Monday
its consolidated profit in the first quarter rose nearly 2 percent
compared with a year earlier, as domestic sales weakened.
   For the period ended June 30, Matsushita's net income was 52.6
billion yen, or about $365 million, from 51.8 billion yen in the
comparable period a year ago. Per-share net income was 24.69 yen, or
about $1.71, up from 24.27 yen.
   Sales for the company, which markets its products worldwide under
the brand names National, Quasar, Panasonic and Technics, were up 6
percent to 1.4 trillion yen, or about $9.72 billion, from 1.319
billion yen.
   While domestic consolidated sales were down slightly, to 789.6
billion yen compared with 798.9 in the year-earlier first quarter,
overseas sales rose 17 percent, thanks to increasing overseas
production, Matsushita said. Overseas sales came to 610.6 billion
yen compared with 520.5 billion yen.
   Matsushita, Japan's largest manufacturer of consumer electric and
electronic products, said that the most rapid growth in consolidated
sales was in ``strategic product areas.''
   These areas include communication and industrial equipment, which
registered sales of 309.1 billion yen, up 16 percent, and electronic
components, including semiconductors, which registered sales of
189.5 billion yen, up 11 percent.
</TEXT>
