Exchange with 720 down, 519 up and 576 unchanged.
   The NYSE composite index of all its listed common stocks declined
to 194.55, down 0.24.
   Volume on the floor of the Big Board came to 59.91 million shares
at midday compared to 90.57 million at the same point on Friday.
   Stocks rebounded from their morning lows after stock-index
futures reached premiums to the cash stock indexes, encouraging
traders to seek profits by selling the futures and buying the
underlying stocks.
   The initial pullback on Wall Street today was viewed as a
continuation of the trend begun Friday following the market's rally
in the previous session. On Thursday, the Dow Jones industrial
average surged about 56{ points to a record 2,734.64.
   W.R. Grace jumped 1\ to 37, responding to a USA Today article
which said several brokerage houses have accumulated Grace shares
for an unidentified client. The company said it was unaware of any
group buying up its shares.
