<FIRST>r f BC-CoalProdn     08-28 0104</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Coal Prodn,0109</SECOND>
<HEAD>Industry Reports Weekly Production</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Only version planned.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic coal production totaled 19.9 million
short tons during the week ending Aug. 19, up slightly from the 19.6
million short tons produced in the previous week, the Department of
Energy reported Monday.
   The U.S. coal industry produced 19.8 million short tons in the
same week last year, according to the department's Energy
Information Administration.
   Domestic coal production so far this year is 602.3 million short
tons, 3 percent ahead of last year's production at this time, the
agency said.
   The week's production accounts for bituminous and lignite coal.
</TEXT>
