<FIRST>r f BC-FedAppointment     08-28 0125</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Fed Appointment,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Battelle Chief Appointed to Cleveland Fed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Douglas E. Olesen, chief executive officer
of the Battelle international research organization, has been
elected a director of the Federal Reserve Bank of Cleveland.
   He will complete the term of Daniel M. Galbreath, president of
John W. Galbreath &amp; Co. of Columbus, who resigned prior to his
term's Dec. 31, 1991 expiration date.
   Election ballots were cast by Fourth District member banks. The
Fourth District includes Ohio, western Pennsylvania, eastern
Kentucky and the northern Panhandle of West Virginia.
   The announcement was made last week.
   The Federal Reserve Bank of Cleveland is one of 12 regional
reserve banks that, along with the board of governors in Washington,
comprise the Federal Reserve System.
</TEXT>
