<FIRST>r f BC-HotelReservations     08-28 0144</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Hotel Reservations,0149</SECOND>
<HEAD>Loews, Covia Announce Joint Hotel Reservation Venture</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Smaller hotel chains and individual inns will be
able to have their own central reservation system through a joint
venture announced Monday by Loews Hotels and Covia, a travel
industry partnership.
   C-LAS, for Covia-Loews Automated Services, ``will offer a
complete set of reservation management options to hotel companies of
every size,'' said Christopher Rockett, Loews Hotels vice president
of marketing.
   Loews and Covia will each own half of the partnership. Terms were
not disclosed.
   The agreement, announced at the National Passenger Traffic
Association annual meeting in Dallas, is expected to be finalized by
the end of the year.
   Loews Hotels is a subsidiary of New York-based Loews Corp. Covia,
based in Rosemont, Ill., is a joint partnership of United Airlines,
USAir, British Airways, KLM Royal Dutch Airlines, Swissair and
Alitalia.
</TEXT>
