<FILEID>AP-NR-08-28-89 2002EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>u f AM-NorthwestFares     08-28 0163</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Northwest Fares,0168</SECOND>
<HEAD>Northwest Cuts Fares to Europe</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EAGAN, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Northwest Airlines cut fares Monday to all
six of its European destinations, lowering some ticket prices to
$144 each way on a roundtrip purchase.
   The reduced fares will range from $144 to $229 each way for
travel beginning between Nov. 1 and March 14 and ending by March 20.
   Reservations will be taken and tickets will be sold until Sept.
15, said Robert Fornaro, vice president of marketing planning.
Destinations are London, Paris, Amsterdam, Frankfurt, Copenhagen and
Glasgow.
   To qualify for the discounts, Northwest passengers must plan
trips to Europe of between six and 21 days and buy a roundtrip
ticket. Limited seats are available on every flight, except during
Thanksgiving and Christmas periods, Fornaro said.
   The lowest fares will be available for passengers who begin their
trips in Boston, Baltimore, Chicago, Detroit, Milwaukee, New York,
Philadelphia and Washington, D.C. Fares from West Coast markets will
be $229 each way.
</TEXT>
